cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper deals with the analysis of diffusion networks on Twitter, which involves social media, network analysis, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SD (Software Engineering), which deals with the development of software systems for social media platforms. The paper also involves the study of social and political backlashes, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The use of algorithms and machine learning techniques for classification purposes suggests the possibility of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) categories.
